Preheat the oven to 200C/180C Fan/Gas 6. Drain the apricots, reserving the juice. Put the apricot halves in a shallow 1 litre/1¾ pint ovenproof dish. Pour over 5 tablespoons of the reserved juice. Coarsely grate the marzipan on top and lightly toss.In a large bowl, rub the flour, oats, sugar and oil together until well combined. Stir in the flaked almonds (if using). Sprinkle the crumble mixture on top of the apricots.Bake for 30–35 minutes, or until the crumble topping is golden-brown and the filling is bubbling up around the sides.Warm the custard in a small saucepan and serve alongside the crumble.